The '''red-vested myzomela''' ('''''Myzomela malaitae'''''), also known as the '''red-bellied myzomela''', is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Meliphagidae]]. It is [[Endemism|endemic]] to [[Malaita]] ([[Solomon Islands]]). Its natural [[habitat]]s are subtropical or tropical moist lowland [[forest]]s and subtropical or tropical moist [[montane forest]]s. It is threatened by [[habitat loss]].

